<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Roger" baseAuthorityYear="1860" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Proceratium" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Proceratium melinum" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melinum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Proceratium melinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is rarely collected due to its subterranean lifestyle and small colonies, although it is widespread in the Palaearctic. It is known in Bulgaria in a small number of localities (Dobrudzha, Thracian Lowland (Svilengrad), Struma Valley (Petrich, Sandanski) and Burgas) (
<bibRefCitation author="Forel, A." journalOrPublisher="Verhandlungen der Zoologisch-Botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" pagination="305 - 318" refId="B7727072" refString="Forel, A., 1892. Die Ameisenfauna Bulgariens. (Nebst biologischen Beobachtungen). Verhandlungen der Zoologisch-Botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien 42: 305 - 318" title="Die Ameisenfauna Bulgariens. (Nebst biologischen Beobachtungen)" volume="42" year="1892">Forel 1892</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Atanassov, N." journalOrPublisher="Bulgarian Academy of Sciences, Sofia" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" refId="B7725616" refString="Atanassov, N., Dlussky, G. M., 1992. Fauna Bulgarica. 22. Hymenoptera, Formicidae. Bulgarian Academy of Sciences, Sofia" title="Fauna Bulgarica. 22. Hymenoptera, Formicidae" year="1992">Atanassov and Dlussky 1992</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Lapeva-Gjonova, A." journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" pagination="1 - 124" refId="B7725831" refString="Lapeva-Gjonova, A., Antonova, V., Radchenko, A. G., Atanasova, M., 2010. Catalogue of the ants (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) of Bulgaria. ZooKeys 62: 1 - 124" title="Catalogue of the ants (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) of Bulgaria" volume="62" year="2010">Lapeva-Gjonova et al. 2010</bibRefCitation>
